President Barack Obama welcomes President Karzai's acceptance of the Independent Electoral Commission's certification of the August 20 election results and his agreement to participate in a second round of the election. Obama believes this is an important step forward in ensuring a credible process for the Afghan people and a government that reflects their will. He congratulates the Afghan people on their patience and resilience throughout the election process and commends both the Independent Electoral Commission and the Electoral Complaints Commission for carrying out their mandates. Obama encourages all elements of Afghan society to come together to advance democracy, peace, and justice, and the United States and the international community are committed to partnering with the Afghan people in this effort.